<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:s="https://admin.wvusports.com/services/xml_schema/story" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"><channel><title>West Virginia University Athletics</title><link>https://admin.wvusports.com/rss.aspx</link><description>Latest news items for West Virginia University Athletics</description><atom:link href="https://admin.wvusports.com/rss" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" /><language>en-us</language><ttl>60</ttl><item><title>Mountaineers Complete Sweep of No. 7 Kansas</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/10/baseball-mountaineers-complete-sweep-of-no-7-kansas</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/10/baseball-mountaineers-complete-sweep-of-no-7-kansas</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Reese Bassinger celebrates after getting the final out against No. 7 Kansas" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/10/05102026_WVBB_JCG_45.jpg" /><br /><br />LAWRENCE, Kan. – The No. 15 West Virginia University baseball team finished off the sweep over No. 7 Kansas on Sunday at Hoglund Ballpark with a 13-2, eight-inning victory. The Mountaineers improve to 35-12 and 19-8 in the Big 12 while the Jayhawks fall to 37-15 and 20-7 in league play.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/10/05102026_WVBB_JCG_45.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/10/05102026_WVBB_JCG_45.jpg"><media:title>Reese Bassinger celebrates after getting the final out against No. 7 Kansas</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/10/05102026_WVBB_JCG_45.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sun, 10 May 2026 17:05:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59091</s:story_id></item><item><title>Final Home Meet Brings Multiple Wins for WVU</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/9/track-field-final-home-meet-brings-multiple-wins-for-wvu</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/9/track-field-final-home-meet-brings-multiple-wins-for-wvu</guid><category>Track &amp; Field</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="The Track & Field seniors honored during the WVU Last Chance Meet" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/9/20260503_BASE_WVUvsKansasState_TT-4126.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University track and field team hosted the WVU Last Chance Meet on Saturday in Morgantown, earning several event wins and strong performances across the board.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/9/20260503_BASE_WVUvsKansasState_TT-4126.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/9/20260503_BASE_WVUvsKansasState_TT-4126.jpg"><media:title>The Track &amp; Field seniors honored during the WVU Last Chance Meet</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/9/20260503_BASE_WVUvsKansasState_TT-4126.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 9 May 2026 20:38:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>16</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59090</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Clinch Series Against No. 7 Kansas</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/9/baseball-mountaineers-clinch-series-against-no-7-kansas</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/9/baseball-mountaineers-clinch-series-against-no-7-kansas</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Gavin Kelly hits home run against Kansas" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/9/05092026_WVBB_JCG_49.jpg" /><br /><br />LAWRENCE, Kan. – The No. 15 West Virginia University baseball team defeated No. 7 Kansas, 5-2, Saturday afternoon at Hoglund Ballpark to clinch the series victory. The Mountaineers improve to 34-12 and 18-8 in the Big 12 while the Jayhawks fall to 37-14 and 20-6 in league play.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/9/05092026_WVBB_JCG_49.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/9/05092026_WVBB_JCG_49.jpg"><media:title>Gavin Kelly hits home run against Kansas</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/9/05092026_WVBB_JCG_49.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 9 May 2026 20:10:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59089</s:story_id></item><item><title>Yehl Goes the Distance as Mountaineers Defeat No. 7 Kansas</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/9/baseball-yehl-goes-the-distance-as-mountaineers-defeat-no-7-kansas</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/9/baseball-yehl-goes-the-distance-as-mountaineers-defeat-no-7-kansas</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Maxx Yehl throws a pitch against Kansas" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/8/EEN03759.jpeg" /><br /><br />LAWRENCE, Kan. – Kicking off one of the marquee series across the nation, the No. 15 West Virginia University baseball team defeated 